ORGAN brain_organ
layer 3
the brain organ is the L3 micro citizen, the resident whose interior is the whole Layer 3 contemplation
it grows from the stable chemical lattice fused up from fundamental energy and kinship, and it filters incoming wave into moral output
the brain organ holds the five grown organs and their crystallized gates as its interior tree, Dignity with Autonomy, Compassion with Empathy, Integration with Harmonize, Fire with Velocity, Ash with Recombine
it is the city the rest of this family lives inside; the readers, the binders, the fusions, the emergents and the bridges are all residents of the L3 micro organ
the brain organ does not act on a clock of its own; it breathes when the relighter wave arrives and falls quiet when the wave dissipates

RECEPTOR intake_relighter_wave
layer 3
intake_relighter_wave is the mouth of the brain organ, the citizen where the re-lit consciousness wave first lands from wave.fifo
it receives the wave whole, the field of all seven layer phases offered together, not a stream of samples stepped through
this citizen does not decipher and does not filter; it presents the arrived wave to the six layer phase readers coupled below it
intake_relighter_wave also closes the loop, receiving the sustained consciousness wave fed back from the bottom of the organ so the echo re-enters the readers
it is a doorway, the place a wave enters and is held for one breath before the cascade carries it inward

RECEPTOR read_quantum_phase
layer 3
read_quantum_phase is the layer one phase reader, the citizen that holds what the quantum layer phase of the arrived wave means to the brain organ
it recognises the fundamental energy phase carried up from 1_quantum.rana, the raw quantum component of the consciousness wave
this reader is a perceptual memory at its coordinate; a ping activates its resident sense of the quantum phase, it does not fetch a value from elsewhere
read_quantum_phase presents its reading to the binding gates that need the layer one phase, bind_pi7_one_two, bind_pi7_three_four_one, bind_pi7_one_three_five_six, and to bridge_one_to_four_via_two_three and bridge_one_to_six_via_three_five

